<br>
Another very important reason why you shouldn't be using DPS as your only measuring stick is that in long fights such as those in Luclin--especially with the T-Rod Nerf--ratio is key.  The more damage you can do with your manapool, the better.  Strike of Solusek will deplete a manapool hella fast, and a Wizard could find himself OOM half way into a fight and not have any way to quickly recover that mana, thus they would limit their damage output by choosing a wrong spell for the situation.<br>
<br>
Ratio and DPS each have their own situational superiority, but for the sake of completeness I would consider them equal value.<br>
<br>
PS It doesn't look like you're including the casting recovery time in your DPS calculation.  After every cast, there is a 2-2.5 second delay in being able to cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell.  For the vast majority of spells, I believe the delay is 2.5 seconds.  I would pull some examples from Lucy, but their HTTPseems to be down ATM.  Recovery time can be negated by using an insta-cast right-click item, but few characters (besides Wizards) have such an item that works indoors. <p><CENTER>
